content.description: Starts out hard at overhang then eases up to mid height where a reachy move has you plugging two pieces to lighten the mood.
content.protection: Single rack cams, nuts, slings and quickdraws
content.location: On the bottom of lower gorge is a west facing wall; climb the right edge/arete.

content.description: The center of the block is a corner with two roofs, the first roof is smaller and the second has an OW move or two to gain the ledge and an easy exit.
content.protection:
Thin nuts, single cams to #4, slings and quickdraws. 

  Rappel single 60m from chains.
content.location: From the creek flat area in the Central Gorge, look north to a  60' tall block high on river right.

content.description: Reachy moves in the center make this ok for taller folks. Head up then trend left to center of wall. Up horizontals with difficult moves in between. Top out on overhung mantle. Shades of the Gunks, this route could be found along the Carriage road!
content.protection: Few cams in fingers, tight hands sizes.
content.location: In center of west facing wall, between Fife's Finger and Wilder Ride is a wide crack. This is the start. Rappel anchor on Sunset Corner.

content.description: Nice right-facing dihedral with fingers and an easy overhang at the finish.
content.protection: single rack of cams, nuts. Gear belay with bolt. Walk off or rappel Sunset Corner.
content.location:
Left most route on west facing wall in the corner. 

  Start on pedestal.

content.description: A nice warm area in winter; if in the shade it's fine other seasons. It faces south and is shaded by the huge wall facing it across the Creek.
